title: Franchise value of the Washington Redskins ( NFL ) 2002 to 2019
yAxis: Franchise value in million U.S. dollars
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Franchise value in million U.S. dollars, containing a total of 18 data points.
Overall Franchise value in million U.S. dollars has increased over the Year.

Franchise value in million U.S. dollars is slightly increasing from 2002 to 2006, roughly constant from 2006 to 2012, gradually increasing from 2012 to 2015, roughly constant from 2015 to 2018, and lastly roughly increasing from 2018 to 2019.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2013 and 2014.
Maximum Franchise value in million U.S. dollars, about 3400.0 was reported at Year 2019
The lowest Franchise value in million U.S. dollars, of value 845.0 was reported at Year 2002
